<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Marsham" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[151,382,581,607]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,382,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mecinus circulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,652,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[151,265,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body elongate, subcylindrical, elytral integument reddish and black to completely black, protibiae with apical part of ventral surface distinctly directed outward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,652,820]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[199,566,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks and comparative notes</emphasis>
. Within this species group, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Marsham" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[891,1041,724,748]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circulatus">
<emphasis box="[891,1041,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. circulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1907" box="[1100,1238,724,748]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1238,724,748]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are undoubtfully sister species due to the shape of the spermatheca as are the pair 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1795" box="[866,996,761,784]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyraster">
<emphasis box="[866,996,761,784]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. pyraster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Caldara &amp; Fogato" authorityYear="2013" box="[1049,1213,760,784]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baridioides">
<emphasis box="[1049,1213,760,784]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">M. baridioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the shape of spermatheca and ventrite 5 of the male having a tuft of hairs at the midline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
